Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.36,0:00:02.96,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}My name's Conan Edogawa!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.96,0:00:06.13,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}High school student Shin'ichi was\Nforced to take a drug that shrunk him.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.13,0:00:08.96,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Although smaller, my mind remains\Nthat of a sharp detective!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.96,0:00:10.70,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Today's case takes place in a high-rise building!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.70,0:00:12.33,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}These elevators bear a crime!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.33,0:00:15.55,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Even when hidden behind double doors,\Nthere's always only one truth!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.20,0:02:03.29,Dialogue Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Emergency Exit"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.83,0:02:13.29,Dialogue Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Fitting Room"
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.45,0:02:36.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, it's a holiday!\NWhy's there so much traffic?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.63,0:02:40.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure it wouldn't\Nhave been faster by train?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.36,0:02:45.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Being a model for Ashiya{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s clothing—\Nit's like a dream come true!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.53,0:02:49.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're sure this is Eiko Ashiya, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.10,0:02:50.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You know that she's—
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.81,0:02:56.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,—one of the top fashion\Ndesigners in Japan... right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.28,0:03:02.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wasn't Eiko Ashiya the one whose\Nfashion show was cancelled recently?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.28,0:03:08.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A rival company announced a winter clothing line
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.39,0:03:11.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,very similar to the latest line that\Nshe was going to have at her show.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.86,0:03:14.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So she had no choice but to cancel it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.33,0:03:17.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You sure know a lot about her!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.23,0:03:21.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me you're actually an Eiko Ashiya fan!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.07,0:03:23.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I had no idea, Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.24,0:03:26.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be silly! A detective must\Nalways expand his horizons
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.21,0:03:30.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,to keep on top of what's going on\Nin the world around him!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.35,0:03:33.62,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Sure...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.62,0:03:35.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Here it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.35,0:03:40.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's one big building...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.09,0:03:45.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're not going to be\Na model yourself, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.96,0:03:49.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I know that! You're really\Nstarting to get on my nerves!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.03,0:03:54.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me! My name's Ran Mouri...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.40,0:03:56.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, we've been expecting you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.27,0:03:59.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The company president will be\Nback soon. Please wait over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.71,0:04:01.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.18,0:04:05.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It certainly is quiet!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.05,0:04:10.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, today's a holiday,\Nso there's no one else here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.22,0:04:13.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so sorry to keep you waiting, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.66,0:04:15.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, that's okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.96,0:04:17.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.61,0:04:18.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.43,0:04:21.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Are big purses the latest style now?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.40,0:04:28.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Her life revolves around all\Nthe up-and-coming fashions!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.20,0:04:30.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure it'll catch on soon!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.51,0:04:34.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm really sorry about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.91,0:04:37.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This is my father and Conan Edogawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.68,0:04:41.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They absolutely insisted on coming with me...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.12,0:04:42.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Kogoro Mouri, at your service.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.55,0:04:44.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for giving my\Ndaughter this opportunity—
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.42,0:04:47.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Kogoro Mouri? The famous detective?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.29,0:04:50.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you've heard of me! What an honor this is!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.29,0:04:53.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,These are a token of my\Nadmiration. Please accept them.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.86,0:04:55.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ashiya{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.36,0:04:58.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.37,0:05:01.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.92,0:05:03.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.24,0:05:06.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This is my secretary, Mika Taniguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.07,0:05:08.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Nice to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.44,0:05:11.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This is Ran Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and her father, Kogoro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.98,0:05:12.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And this here is...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.85,0:05:15.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan Edogawa!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.18,0:05:17.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Right! Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.12,0:05:20.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry to call you here on a Sunday.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.62,0:05:25.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's okay. I'll just quit as soon as I can.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.73,0:05:31.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After all, I am being forced\Nto work on weekends now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.60,0:05:34.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Fine. Whatever you like.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.64,0:05:41.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll just go put these flowers in my office\Nand bring back the paperwork.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.24,0:05:46.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Please have a seat there with your father\Nand Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} while you wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.28,0:05:48.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Certainly!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.28,0:05:53.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mika{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}. Go to the eighth-floor\Nfitting room and get ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.39,0:05:55.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,See you shortly.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.16,0:06:02.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me, but is that secretary quitting?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.03,0:06:06.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. She's apparently already\Nturned in her letter of resignation.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.17,0:06:11.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They seem on such bad terms,\Nbut she still pushed the button for her.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.29,0:06:17.29,Dialogue Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Direct elevator to the 15th floor"
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.96,0:06:24.00,Dialogue Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Direct elevator to the 8th floor (Stops at each floor coming down)"
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.59,0:06:26.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, let's wait over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.29,0:06:27.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But first I need to use the bathroom!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.45,0:06:29.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Same here!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.76,0:06:32.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry up and go!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.89,0:06:35.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That feels much better!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.00,0:06:37.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you both remember to wash your hands?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.67,0:06:43.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Eda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.87,0:06:45.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.74,0:06:50.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I called Mika{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s cell phone from\Nmy office, but she won't answer!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.71,0:06:52.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Will you come look with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.25,0:06:53.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.35,0:06:57.55,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Why's she so worked up about\Nsomeone not answering their phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.55,0:06:59.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.09,0:07:04.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The elevator Taniguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} used\Nis stuck on the 8th floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.49,0:07:06.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Could something have happened to her?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.19,0:07:11.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,For now, let's take this elevator up\Nand see for ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.22,0:07:32.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter, Eiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.23,0:07:41.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The secretary, Mika Taniguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.60,0:07:44.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait! There are footprints on the floor!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.97,0:07:46.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Footprints...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.34,0:07:54.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It would seem they were made\Nby dust from the emergency stairs!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.04,0:07:55.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A robber must've broke inside!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.14,0:07:59.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They snuck in, found Mika{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},\Nand then stabbed her!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.01,0:08:04.35,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}It's almost like she {\i1}knew{\i0} this\Nwould happen to Taniguchi{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10}...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.72,0:08:08.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Eda{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}! Could you stop the door?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.10,0:08:09.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.17,0:08:21.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe this...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.08,0:08:29.31,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}These footprints...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.18,0:08:39.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Stabbed through the heart. Died almost instantly.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.05,0:08:41.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.06,0:08:43.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,These footprints are 26 centimeters in length.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.99,0:08:45.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,26 centimeters, eh...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.73,0:08:47.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It must've been a man.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.93,0:08:53.80,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}There's a blood stain on her shoulder...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.80,0:08:59.01,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}And what's this crease doing\Non the shoulder of her jacket?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.01,0:09:02.24,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Would someone working in the\Noverly-conscious fashion industry
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.24,0:09:06.48,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}wear something with a crease like that there?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.48,0:09:09.85,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}But the strangest thing is that\NTaniguchi{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} is lying on the ground
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.85,0:09:13.02,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}facing {\i1}away{\i0} from the elevator.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.02,0:09:16.29,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}If she was stabbed as she got off the elevator,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.29,0:09:19.36,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}she would have collapsed inside it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.36,0:09:28.04,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}In which case, the killer must've\Npurposely pulled her into the hallway.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.04,0:09:31.97,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}But why would they need to do that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.84,0:09:39.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You and Taniguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} were riding\Nin different elevators, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.71,0:09:43.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. That elevator was the one I took.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.65,0:09:47.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The 15th floor?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.72,0:09:50.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This goes non-stop to the 15th floor?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.39,0:09:52.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.03,0:09:56.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And this center elevator is the one Mika Taniguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} took?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.87,0:09:59.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That one's non-stop to the 8th floor,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.07,0:10:02.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and then it can go floor-by-floor,\Nall the way to the 15th floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.60,0:10:05.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And then the one we took just now\Nstops at the 8th floor,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.04,0:10:07.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,then comes back down\Nin single-floor increments...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.94,0:10:09.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.14,0:10:12.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Only two elevators can go to the 15th floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.81,0:10:17.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,How much time passed from when\NAshiya{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} first got into the elevator
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.39,0:10:19.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and until she returned here?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.42,0:10:20.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Two minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.72,0:10:23.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, a little more than one minute, I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.86,0:10:25.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A little under two minutes...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.49,0:10:26.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.49,0:10:34.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The emergency stairwell exit\Non the 1st floor was unlocked.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.70,0:10:36.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When did you last do your rounds?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.24,0:10:38.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,About 2 hours before the incident.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.57,0:10:41.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm certain the door was locked then!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.41,0:10:44.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Did anyone enter or leave\Nthe building afterwards?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.41,0:10:48.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody except the company president.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.12,0:10:51.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I needed to check something.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.02,0:10:55.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I arrived about an hour ago and\Nwas in my office for half an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.02,0:10:58.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After that, I left to get some coffee.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.23,0:11:00.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I left through the main entrance, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.16,0:11:03.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector! I think Eiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is right—
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.47,0:11:05.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,this was the work of a burglar\Nbreaking into the building!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.67,0:11:09.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The killer unlocked the 1st floor\Nemergency exit from the outside
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.40,0:11:12.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and took the stairs to the 8th floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.01,0:11:15.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, just as he passed by the elevators...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.48,0:11:17.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...he ran into Taniguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.35,0:11:27.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He murdered her, then\Nescaped back down the stairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.82,0:11:31.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright! Search the nearby vicinity immediately!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.46,0:11:34.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Also, I'll need to take your\Nfingerprints, Ashiya{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.93,0:11:38.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you implying that I'm the murderer?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.30,0:11:39.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing of the sort!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.50,0:11:42.40,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's to distinguish between the\Nkiller's fingerprints and yours!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.40,0:11:46.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, there's no way you could\Npossibly have been the murderer!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.98,0:11:49.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.84,0:11:52.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you stupid or something?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.35,0:11:53.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Pay attention, now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.21,0:11:58.19,Dialogue Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Eiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and Taniguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} got in\Ndifferent elevators at the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.67,0:11:56.67,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Eiko
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.67,0:11:56.67,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Taniguchi
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.19,0:12:00.46,Dialogue Top,,0000,0000,0000,,Taniguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} arrived at the 8th floor
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.46,0:12:03.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and was murdered immediately\Nafter the doors opened.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.16,0:12:05.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Meanwhile, Eiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was on the 15th floor...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.53,0:12:08.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...and there was no elevator\Nto take her to the 8th floor!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.00,0:12:10.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So how could she have killed Taniguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.90,0:12:14.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But that doesn't clear her of all suspicion—
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.44,0:12:17.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're just a kid; don't tell\Na pro how to do his job!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.07,0:12:19.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's no excuse for hitting him, Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.21,0:12:22.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But he just won't learn!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.14,0:12:24.68,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}What a lost cause!\NCan't depend on him at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.68,0:12:25.68,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Here goes!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.68,0:12:27.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}! Where are you going?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.46,0:12:28.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Forget about him!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.26,0:12:42.42,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}If I'm right, the key to solving this case\Nshould be on the 15th floor!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.43,0:12:48.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow! The company president's floor sure is nice!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.70,0:12:51.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What fancy carpeting!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.84,0:12:58.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A flower petal?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.02,0:13:05.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Pollen...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.73,0:13:13.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.60,0:13:15.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Tape marks!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.96,0:13:19.13,Dialogue Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"President's Office"
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.75,0:13:35.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the same pollen.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.65,0:13:37.42,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.42,0:13:40.86,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Why was there a flower petal and pollen here?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.86,0:13:45.36,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}She wouldn't have passed by here\Nif she went straight to her office...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.36,0:13:50.03,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Taniguchi{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} was killed inside\Nthis elevator, on the 8th floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.03,0:13:53.37,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Eiko Ashiya{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} was all by\Nherself for just over a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.37,0:13:59.64,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Taking the stairs to the 8th floor,\Nkilling her, and then coming back up
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.64,0:14:02.11,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}would take at least 4 or 5 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.11,0:14:06.17,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Meaning that the question here\Nis where exactly she was killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.12,0:14:12.05,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The way her body was lying on the ground...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.05,0:14:15.86,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The blood stain and the unnaturally\Ncrumpled part of her jacket...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.86,0:14:18.33,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The flower petal lying on the floor...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.33,0:14:21.76,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}And the tape marks around\Nthe call button for the elevator
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.76,0:14:23.99,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}that Taniguchi{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10} was in...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.90,0:14:26.97,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}That's it! Now I get it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.97,0:14:30.34,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}This is an alibi trick involving elevators!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.34,0:14:35.14,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Taniguchi{\rHonorifics - Thoughts\be10}-san{\r\be10}'s murderer was indeed Eiko Ashiya!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.86,0:14:41.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No fingerprints at all?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.53,0:14:47.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Nope. There were none on the knife\Nnor on the 1st floor emergency exit.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.24,0:14:51.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me, Inspector.\NWould it be all right if I went home?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.81,0:14:55.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course. That should be enough for today—
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.81,0:15:00.15,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Oh no! If she goes, she'll dispose of the evidence!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.15,0:15:04.92,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I have no other choice!\NI'll have to use the old man again!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.92,0:15:06.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.10,0:15:06.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.89,0:15:08.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, but can we do this another day?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.95,0:15:10.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No problem!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.36,0:15:12.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I'll just be going now...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.25,0:15:14.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Allow me to see you to the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.50,0:15:19.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Not again...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.71,0:15:25.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...Which is what I would like to say,\Nbut we cannot allow you to leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.61,0:15:28.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The reason being...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.95,0:15:32.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...that you're the one who murdered Mika Taniguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.96,0:15:38.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.96,0:15:41.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.16,0:15:46.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You were the one who just explained\Nwhy she couldn't have done it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.10,0:15:47.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.77,0:15:50.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But that was a trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.24,0:15:51.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A trick?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.77,0:15:57.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But first, allow me to explain those\Nfootprints in the 8th floor hallway.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.41,0:15:59.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Have a seat, if you would.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.68,0:16:05.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That was a ruse she concocted\Nto make Mika Taniguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s murder
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.15,0:16:08.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,look like the result of a burglar breaking in.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.95,0:16:12.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Try to remember what\Nthose footprints looked like.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.02,0:16:15.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Normally, someone would run away\Nafter committing a murder, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.59,0:16:18.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This would cause the footprints to be far apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.36,0:16:21.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,However, these footprints were\Nmade by someone walking
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.83,0:16:24.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,on both their way into and out of the building.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.14,0:16:27.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Now that you mention it, you're right...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.07,0:16:28.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Eiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.51,0:16:31.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You entered the building\Nan hour before the murder,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.58,0:16:33.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,made the fake footprints,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.48,0:16:39.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and then unlocked the 1st floor\Nemergency exit from the inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.15,0:16:44.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After this, you hid the sneakers that\Ndon't fit you inside your large purse
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.16,0:16:46.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and then left the building.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.53,0:16:51.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You came back 30 minutes later,\Nafter you had disposed of the sneakers.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.26,0:16:54.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And then as we looked on,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.00,0:16:58.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,you headed for the elevator\Nhall with Mika Taniguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.24,0:17:01.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You were the one who pressed the call button.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.44,0:17:06.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The reason being that you needed her\Nto use the center elevator
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.55,0:17:11.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,instead of the one that was nearest to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.15,0:17:18.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Inside the elevator, you started dialing\Nher number on your cell phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.42,0:17:22.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After getting off on the 15th floor,\Nyou pressed the dial button.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.23,0:17:27.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's hard for cell phones to connect\Nwhile inside elevators, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.80,0:17:35.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You told Taniguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to come\Nto the 15th floor right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.31,0:17:42.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Meanwhile, you taped a coin to\Nthe call button on the 15th floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.92,0:17:47.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You did this to make sure the\Nelevator doors wouldn't close
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.19,0:17:49.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,while you were killing her.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.19,0:17:53.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.69,0:17:57.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}! The victim was\Nfound dead on the 8th floor!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.33,0:18:01.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Now we come to the main point of the trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.53,0:18:06.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you find the direction\Nshe was lying strange?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.21,0:18:10.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If she had been stabbed by someone\Nas she was getting off the elevator,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.34,0:18:12.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,she would have fallen back into it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.95,0:18:17.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But she was lying outside of the\Nelevator, facing away from it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.05,0:18:20.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that you mention it...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.35,0:18:23.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Eiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} stabbed Taniguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} on the 15th floor,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.46,0:18:28.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,got behind her, and then turned her\Nin the direction of the hallway.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.93,0:18:30.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then she pressed the button for the 8th floor
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.83,0:18:33.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and removed the tape from the call button.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.97,0:18:38.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She then propped Taniguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} up\Nin a sitting position
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.84,0:18:43.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and sent her down to the 8th floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.98,0:18:52.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe she would do such a thing...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.25,0:18:57.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There were two keys to unraveling\Nthe mystery behind this alibi trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.39,0:19:01.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The first was the crease on the\Nshoulder of Taniguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s jacket.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.66,0:19:07.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was created when the jacket was\Ncaught between the elevator doors.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.07,0:19:12.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The second key was in the flower\Npetal and pollen left on the carpet
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.24,0:19:14.24,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,when Eiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} put the bouquet on the floor
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.24,0:19:17.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so it wouldn't get in the way of killing Taniguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.54,0:19:19.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's an interesting story.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.71,0:19:23.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But it's nothing but a theory.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.22,0:19:28.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, if Taniguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} rode the\N8th floor elevator a second time,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.02,0:19:32.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,her fingerprint should have\Nbeen on the 8th floor call button.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.16,0:19:33.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, Inspector?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.93,0:19:35.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Any fingerprints on the call button?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.85,0:19:39.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No. No fingerprints at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.70,0:19:43.94,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.\NMika{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} didn't go to the 15th floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.94,0:19:46.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Your theory has been disproved!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.10,0:19:49.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Indeed. Because you removed\Nher fingerprint yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.64,0:19:51.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Truly stupendous execution, it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.84,0:19:56.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In order to close the elevator doors,\Nyou pressed the call button
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.18,0:19:58.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and then removed her\Nfingerprint by wiping it off.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.52,0:20:02.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a minute! Does that mean there's no proof?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.45,0:20:04.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, there's proof all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.66,0:20:07.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Inside Eiko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s purse!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.06,0:20:11.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of proof?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.06,0:20:14.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The bloody gloves she used\Nwhen committing the murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.13,0:20:18.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Time-wise, she shouldn't have\Nbeen able to dispose of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.34,0:20:21.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And she couldn't dare hide\Nthem inside the building.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.81,0:20:25.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You were more than confident\Nabout your elevator alibi trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.88,0:20:29.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In other words, the only possibility\Nis that the bloodied gloves
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.65,0:20:32.68,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,are in your possession!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.68,0:20:37.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The one who stole your design\Nand sold it to that rival company...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.12,0:20:39.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...was Mika Taniguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.56,0:20:45.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're right. The evidence is here, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.50,0:20:49.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But I did it because she had betrayed me.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.30,0:20:51.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,She said she didn't care if I went to the police
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.17,0:20:53.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,because after canceling my fashion show,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.51,0:20:57.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,doing so would only damage the\NEiko Ashiya brand name even more.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.38,0:21:00.84,Dialogue Top,,0000,0000,0000,,"Letter of Resignation"
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.61,0:21:01.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then she tried to quit the company.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.08,0:21:05.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I decided to kill her while\Nshe was still with the company.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.65,0:21:08.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And that was today...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.12,0:21:14.33,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When I heard your father was the\Nfamous detective Kogoro Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.33,0:21:16.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't know what to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.80,0:21:19.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But I didn't have a change of heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.27,0:23:05.64,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.64,0:23:09.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You may not believe me,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.21,0:23:13.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but I was telling the truth when I\Ntold you why I wanted you as a model.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.65,0:23:16.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted someone with a healthy\Nmind and body such as yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.95,0:23:20.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,to wear Eiko Ashiya clothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.06,0:23:27.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so sorry, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.36,0:23:29.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You almost had your chance to be a model...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.73,0:23:32.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No, that's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.73,0:23:35.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? Come to think of it, where's Dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.34,0:23:38.57,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Whoops! I left him there, asleep!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.34,0:23:45.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks like this case has taken its toll on him...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.75,0:23:49.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After all, he's a fan of Eiko Ashiya{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},\Nand he just exposed her crime!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.12,0:23:57.28,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}If he found out I was the one who\Nexposed her crime, he'd murder me!
